<paragraph blockId="53.[189,310,1483,1509]" box="[189,310,1483,1509]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,310,1483,1509]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,1483,1509]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="53.[189,1399,1530,1732]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
The female of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Davies" authorityYear="2005" box="[365,488,1530,1557]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Scrapter" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sittybon">
<emphasis box="[365,488,1530,1557]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">S. sittybon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is here described for the first time. It can be separated from other species of this group by the combination of the following characters: fore tibia entirely or dominantly yellowish to reddish brown, stigma brown, apical margins of metasomal terga broadly brownish translucent (
<figureCitation captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="54.[189,231,1966,1992]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,590,1921]" captionTargetId="figure@54.[189,1399,590,1922]" captionTargetPageId="54" captionText="Fig. 28. Scrapter sittybon Davies, 2005, ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Metasoma (dorsal view). C. Head. D. Head (SEM). E. Thorax (dorsal view). F. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860655" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860655/files/figure.png" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Fig. 28B</figureCitation>
). The male is characterized by an unmodified antenna, scutum between punctures smooth and shiny, the form of S7 (
<figureCitation box="[459,570,1671,1697]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="56.[189,232,1930,1956]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,575,1908]" captionTargetId="figure@56.[189,1398,574,1909]" captionTargetPageId="56" captionText="Fig. 29. Scrapter sittybon Davies, 2005, ♂. A. Lateral view. B. Genitalia (dorsal view, SEM). C. Metasoma (dorsal view). D. S7 (dorsal view, SEM). E. Hind tibia. F. S8, apical end (SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860657" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860657/files/figure.png" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Fig. 29D</figureCitation>
), hind basitarsus blackish and hind tibia apically slightly swollen and curved (
<figureCitation box="[285,391,1706,1732]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="56.[189,232,1930,1956]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,575,1908]" captionTargetId="figure@56.[189,1398,574,1909]" captionTargetPageId="56" captionText="Fig. 29. Scrapter sittybon Davies, 2005, ♂. A. Lateral view. B. Genitalia (dorsal view, SEM). C. Metasoma (dorsal view). D. S7 (dorsal view, SEM). E. Hind tibia. F. S8, apical end (SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860657" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860657/files/figure.png" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Fig. 29E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
