<paragraph blockId="54.[189,334,267,293]" box="[189,334,267,293]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,334,267,293]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,334,267,293]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="54.[189,506,314,375]" box="[234,325,314,340]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[234,325,314,340]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Female</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="54.[189,506,314,375]" box="[189,506,348,375]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
BODY LENGTH. 
<quantity box="[357,501,348,375]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" metricValueMax="5.1" metricValueMin="4.9" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" unit="mm" value="5.0" valueMax="5.1" valueMin="4.9">4.9–5.1 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="54.[189,1399,414,546]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
HEAD. Head wider than long. Integument black, except part of mandibles dark reddish-brown. Face sparsely covered with long, greyish, erect hair (
<figureCitation box="[799,915,449,475]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="54.[189,231,1966,1992]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,590,1921]" captionTargetId="figure@54.[189,1399,590,1922]" captionTargetPageId="54" captionText="Fig. 28. Scrapter sittybon Davies, 2005, ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Metasoma (dorsal view). C. Head. D. Head (SEM). E. Thorax (dorsal view). F. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860655" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860655/files/figure.png" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Fig. 28C</figureCitation>
). Clypeus slightly convex with coarse punctation, apically coarser and sparser (i = 1–2 d), basally much finer and denser (i ˂ 0.5 d); surface between punctures apically smooth and shiny, basally superficially sculptured and slightly matt (
<figureCitation box="[1351,1399,520,546]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="54.[189,231,1966,1992]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,590,1921]" captionTargetId="figure@54.[189,1399,590,1922]" captionTargetPageId="54" captionText="Fig. 28. Scrapter sittybon Davies, 2005, ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Metasoma (dorsal view). C. Head. D. Head (SEM). E. Thorax (dorsal view). F. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860655" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860655/files/figure.png" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Fig.</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860655" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3860655" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860655/files/figure.png" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" startId="54.[189,231,1966,1992]" targetBox="[189,1399,590,1921]" targetPageId="54">
<paragraph blockId="54.[189,1399,1966,2029]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,277,1966,1992]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Fig. 28.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Davies, 2005" authorityName="Davies" authorityYear="2005" box="[284,639,1966,1993]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Scrapter" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sittybon">
<emphasis box="[284,480,1966,1993]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Scrapter sittybon</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Davies G. B. P. &amp; Eardley C. D. &amp; Brothers D. J." box="[486,639,1966,1993]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" pagination="141 - 179" refId="ref26814" refString="Davies G. B. P., Eardley C. D. &amp; Brothers D. J. 2005. Eight new species of Scrapter (Hymenoptera: Apoidea: Colletidae), with descriptions of S. albifumus and S. amplispinatus females and a major range extension of the genus. African Invertebrates 46: 141 - 179." type="journal article" year="2005">Davies, 2005</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, ♀. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[684,705,1966,1992]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">A</emphasis>
. Lateral view. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[873,892,1967,1993]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">B</emphasis>
. Metasoma (dorsal view). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1195,1216,1966,1992]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">C</emphasis>
. Head. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1303,1324,1967,1993]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">D</emphasis>
. Head (SEM). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[281,300,2002,2028]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">E</emphasis>
. Thorax (dorsal view). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[569,587,2002,2028]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">F</emphasis>
. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="55.[189,1398,267,329]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
28C–D). Malar area medially narrow, almost linear. Antenna dorsally darker orange-brown, ventrally more yellowish-brown (
<figureCitation box="[471,579,302,329]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="54.[189,231,1966,1992]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,590,1921]" captionTargetId="figure@54.[189,1399,590,1922]" captionTargetPageId="54" captionText="Fig. 28. Scrapter sittybon Davies, 2005, ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Metasoma (dorsal view). C. Head. D. Head (SEM). E. Thorax (dorsal view). F. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860655" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860655/files/figure.png" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Fig. 28C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="55.[189,1399,368,570]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
MESOSOMA. Integument black, except pronotal lobe and tegula yellowish to reddish-brown (
<figureCitation box="[1275,1386,368,394]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="54.[189,231,1966,1992]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,590,1921]" captionTargetId="figure@54.[189,1399,590,1922]" captionTargetPageId="54" captionText="Fig. 28. Scrapter sittybon Davies, 2005, ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Metasoma (dorsal view). C. Head. D. Head (SEM). E. Thorax (dorsal view). F. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860655" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860655/files/figure.png" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Fig. 28A</figureCitation>
). Mesoscutal disc between punctures polished and shiny; disc densely (i = 1–2 d) and coarsely punctate, punctures of variable size (
<figureCitation box="[520,609,438,464]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="54.[189,231,1966,1992]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,590,1921]" captionTargetId="figure@54.[189,1399,590,1922]" captionTargetPageId="54" captionText="Fig. 28. Scrapter sittybon Davies, 2005, ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Metasoma (dorsal view). C. Head. D. Head (SEM). E. Thorax (dorsal view). F. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860655" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860655/files/figure.png" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Fig. 28</figureCitation>
E–F). Metanotum about 2/3 as long as basal area of propodeum, apically with distinct carinate depression (
<figureCitation box="[689,794,473,500]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="54.[189,231,1966,1992]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,590,1921]" captionTargetId="figure@54.[189,1399,590,1922]" captionTargetPageId="54" captionText="Fig. 28. Scrapter sittybon Davies, 2005, ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Metasoma (dorsal view). C. Head. D. Head (SEM). E. Thorax (dorsal view). F. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860655" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860655/files/figure.png" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Fig. 28F</figureCitation>
). Propodeum basally coarsely and broadly carinate (
<figureCitation box="[198,303,509,535]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="54.[189,231,1966,1992]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,590,1921]" captionTargetId="figure@54.[189,1399,590,1922]" captionTargetPageId="54" captionText="Fig. 28. Scrapter sittybon Davies, 2005, ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Metasoma (dorsal view). C. Head. D. Head (SEM). E. Thorax (dorsal view). F. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860655" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860655/files/figure.png" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Fig. 28F</figureCitation>
). Mesoscutum, scutellum, metanotum, mesepisternum and propodeum sparsely covered with short, greyish, erect hair (
<figureCitation box="[489,600,544,570]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="54.[189,231,1966,1992]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,590,1921]" captionTargetId="figure@54.[189,1399,590,1922]" captionTargetPageId="54" captionText="Fig. 28. Scrapter sittybon Davies, 2005, ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Metasoma (dorsal view). C. Head. D. Head (SEM). E. Thorax (dorsal view). F. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860655" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860655/files/figure.png" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Fig. 28A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="55.[189,986,609,636]" box="[189,986,609,636]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">WINGS. Slightly yellowish-brown; wing venation and stigma brown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="55.[189,1399,675,771]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
LEGS. Integument mostly dark reddish-brown, partly blackish; fore tibia and tarsi almost completely, mid tibia anteriorly and hind tibia basally yellowish-brown (
<figureCitation box="[909,1021,710,736]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="54.[189,231,1966,1992]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,590,1921]" captionTargetId="figure@54.[189,1399,590,1922]" captionTargetPageId="54" captionText="Fig. 28. Scrapter sittybon Davies, 2005, ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Metasoma (dorsal view). C. Head. D. Head (SEM). E. Thorax (dorsal view). F. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860655" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860655/files/figure.png" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Fig. 28A</figureCitation>
). Vestiture greyish-white, scopa greyish-white.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="55.[189,1398,811,1013]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
METASOMA. Integument black, apical margins of terga broadly translucent yellowish to reddish-brown (
<figureCitation box="[198,305,846,872]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="54.[189,231,1966,1992]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,590,1921]" captionTargetId="figure@54.[189,1399,590,1922]" captionTargetPageId="54" captionText="Fig. 28. Scrapter sittybon Davies, 2005, ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Metasoma (dorsal view). C. Head. D. Head (SEM). E. Thorax (dorsal view). F. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860655" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860655/files/figure.png" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Fig. 28B</figureCitation>
). Discs of T1 and T2 without hair; following terga with very sparse and short but increasingly more and longer hair; apical tergal hair bands missing on all terga (
<figureCitation box="[980,1088,881,907]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="54.[189,231,1966,1992]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,590,1921]" captionTargetId="figure@54.[189,1399,590,1922]" captionTargetPageId="54" captionText="Fig. 28. Scrapter sittybon Davies, 2005, ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Metasoma (dorsal view). C. Head. D. Head (SEM). E. Thorax (dorsal view). F. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860655" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860655/files/figure.png" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Fig. 28B</figureCitation>
). Prepygidial and pygidial fimbriae greyish-brown. T1 and following terga densely (i = 1 d) but almost invisibly very finely and irregularly punctate, between punctures sculptured and slightly matt; T2–T4 with superficially sculptured but shiny, broad apical tergal depression (
<figureCitation box="[677,784,987,1013]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="54.[189,231,1966,1992]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,590,1921]" captionTargetId="figure@54.[189,1399,590,1922]" captionTargetPageId="54" captionText="Fig. 28. Scrapter sittybon Davies, 2005, ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Metasoma (dorsal view). C. Head. D. Head (SEM). E. Thorax (dorsal view). F. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860655" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860655/files/figure.png" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Fig. 28B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="55.[189,506,1052,1114]" box="[234,298,1052,1078]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[234,298,1052,1078]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Male</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="55.[189,506,1052,1114]" box="[189,506,1087,1114]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
BODY LENGTH. 
<quantity box="[357,501,1087,1114]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" metricValueMax="5.2" metricValueMin="4.8" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" unit="mm" value="5.0" valueMax="5.2" valueMin="4.8">4.8–5.2 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="55.[189,1399,1153,1285]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
HEAD. Head slightly wider than long. Integument black, except mandible partly dark reddish-brown. Face densely covered with long, greyish-white, erect hair. Malar area medially narrow, almost linear. Antennal flagellum either completely yellowish-brown or sometimes dorsally dark brown, particularly the last 3–4 segments dorsally (
<figureCitation box="[559,669,1258,1284]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="56.[189,232,1930,1956]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,575,1908]" captionTargetId="figure@56.[189,1398,574,1909]" captionTargetPageId="56" captionText="Fig. 29. Scrapter sittybon Davies, 2005, ♂. A. Lateral view. B. Genitalia (dorsal view, SEM). C. Metasoma (dorsal view). D. S7 (dorsal view, SEM). E. Hind tibia. F. S8, apical end (SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860657" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860657/files/figure.png" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Fig. 29A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="55.[189,1398,1324,1421]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
MESOSOMA. Integument black, tegula yellowish-brown. Mesoscutal disc between punctures smooth and shiny; disc densely (i = 0.5–1.0 d) and finely punctate. Mesoscutum, scutellum, metanotum, mesepisternum and propodeum covered with long, yellowish-grey, erect hair (
<figureCitation box="[1106,1216,1394,1420]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="56.[189,232,1930,1956]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,575,1908]" captionTargetId="figure@56.[189,1398,574,1909]" captionTargetPageId="56" captionText="Fig. 29. Scrapter sittybon Davies, 2005, ♂. A. Lateral view. B. Genitalia (dorsal view, SEM). C. Metasoma (dorsal view). D. S7 (dorsal view, SEM). E. Hind tibia. F. S8, apical end (SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860657" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860657/files/figure.png" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Fig. 29A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="55.[189,986,1460,1486]" box="[189,986,1460,1486]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">WINGS. Slightly yellowish-brown; wing venation and stigma brown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="55.[189,1399,1525,1622]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
LEGS. Integument mostly dark yellowish to reddish-black, fore tibia and tarsi, mid tibia (except darker spot posteriorly), base of hind tibia and femora apically yellow to yellowish-brown (
<figureCitation box="[1206,1318,1560,1586]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="56.[189,232,1930,1956]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,575,1908]" captionTargetId="figure@56.[189,1398,574,1909]" captionTargetPageId="56" captionText="Fig. 29. Scrapter sittybon Davies, 2005, ♂. A. Lateral view. B. Genitalia (dorsal view, SEM). C. Metasoma (dorsal view). D. S7 (dorsal view, SEM). E. Hind tibia. F. S8, apical end (SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860657" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860657/files/figure.png" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Fig. 29A</figureCitation>
). Hind tibia inside apically slightly broadened and curved (
<figureCitation box="[797,903,1595,1622]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="56.[189,232,1930,1956]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,575,1908]" captionTargetId="figure@56.[189,1398,574,1909]" captionTargetPageId="56" captionText="Fig. 29. Scrapter sittybon Davies, 2005, ♂. A. Lateral view. B. Genitalia (dorsal view, SEM). C. Metasoma (dorsal view). D. S7 (dorsal view, SEM). E. Hind tibia. F. S8, apical end (SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860657" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860657/files/figure.png" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Fig. 29E</figureCitation>
). Vestiture greyish-white.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="55.[189,1399,1661,1899]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
METASOMA. Integument black, apical margins of terga broadly translucent yellowish to reddish-brown (
<figureCitation box="[198,308,1696,1722]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="56.[189,232,1930,1956]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,575,1908]" captionTargetId="figure@56.[189,1398,574,1909]" captionTargetPageId="56" captionText="Fig. 29. Scrapter sittybon Davies, 2005, ♂. A. Lateral view. B. Genitalia (dorsal view, SEM). C. Metasoma (dorsal view). D. S7 (dorsal view, SEM). E. Hind tibia. F. S8, apical end (SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860657" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860657/files/figure.png" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Fig. 29C</figureCitation>
). Discs of T1–T3 without hair; following terga with very short and sparse but increasingly more and longer hair; T2–T4 basally with a broad and dense band of very fine but long, erect, silverish hair; apical tergal hair bands missing on all terga (
<figureCitation box="[775,883,1766,1793]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="56.[189,232,1930,1956]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,575,1908]" captionTargetId="figure@56.[189,1398,574,1909]" captionTargetPageId="56" captionText="Fig. 29. Scrapter sittybon Davies, 2005, ♂. A. Lateral view. B. Genitalia (dorsal view, SEM). C. Metasoma (dorsal view). D. S7 (dorsal view, SEM). E. Hind tibia. F. S8, apical end (SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860657" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860657/files/figure.png" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Fig. 29C</figureCitation>
). T1 and following terga irregularly densely (i ˂ 0.5–1 d) but almost invisibly very finely punctate, between punctures sculptured and slightly matt; terga with broad, superficially sculptured but shiny apical tergal depression (
<figureCitation box="[1072,1179,1837,1863]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="56.[189,232,1930,1956]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,575,1908]" captionTargetId="figure@56.[189,1398,574,1909]" captionTargetPageId="56" captionText="Fig. 29. Scrapter sittybon Davies, 2005, ♂. A. Lateral view. B. Genitalia (dorsal view, SEM). C. Metasoma (dorsal view). D. S7 (dorsal view, SEM). E. Hind tibia. F. S8, apical end (SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860657" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860657/files/figure.png" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Fig. 29C</figureCitation>
). S3–S5 with long, sparse apical hair fringes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="55.[189,1330,1937,1964]" box="[189,1330,1937,1964]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
TERMINALIA. Genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[460,567,1937,1964]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="56.[189,232,1930,1956]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,575,1908]" captionTargetId="figure@56.[189,1398,574,1909]" captionTargetPageId="56" captionText="Fig. 29. Scrapter sittybon Davies, 2005, ♂. A. Lateral view. B. Genitalia (dorsal view, SEM). C. Metasoma (dorsal view). D. S7 (dorsal view, SEM). E. Hind tibia. F. S8, apical end (SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860657" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860657/files/figure.png" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Fig. 29B</figureCitation>
), S7 (
<figureCitation box="[636,743,1937,1964]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="56.[189,232,1930,1956]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,575,1908]" captionTargetId="figure@56.[189,1398,574,1909]" captionTargetPageId="56" captionText="Fig. 29. Scrapter sittybon Davies, 2005, ♂. A. Lateral view. B. Genitalia (dorsal view, SEM). C. Metasoma (dorsal view). D. S7 (dorsal view, SEM). E. Hind tibia. F. S8, apical end (SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860657" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860657/files/figure.png" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Fig. 29D</figureCitation>
) and terminal plate of S8 (
<figureCitation box="[1056,1158,1937,1964]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="56.[189,232,1930,1956]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,575,1908]" captionTargetId="figure@56.[189,1398,574,1909]" captionTargetPageId="56" captionText="Fig. 29. Scrapter sittybon Davies, 2005, ♂. A. Lateral view. B. Genitalia (dorsal view, SEM). C. Metasoma (dorsal view). D. S7 (dorsal view, SEM). E. Hind tibia. F. S8, apical end (SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860657" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860657/files/figure.png" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Fig. 29F</figureCitation>
) as illustrated.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
